{"key":"post-9780476","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9780476</id>\n<content>&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;but i was wondering, i have an old pickle jar, i washed it really good and washed it with 91% rubbing alcohol. should that be enough in terms of having it sterilized?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Soap and water is all you need to wash any jar out with, even if it's had mold in it.&amp;nbsp; However, a pickle jar is going to be too large.&amp;nbsp; You want to use 1/2 pint jars.&amp;nbsp; For every success with 1 pint jars, there's ten failures, and I don't know of ANYONE who's ever grown a brf cake larger than 1 pint, let alone a pickle jar which is usually at least a quart.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Go to the grocery store and buy a dozen 1/2 pint wide mouth mason jars for $8 and use those.&amp;nbsp; Here's a video and some text for you that explains the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer noopener&quot;&gt;brf tek.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9780495</next>\n<prev>9780443</prev>\n<first>9780313</first>\n<last>9815805</last>\n<when>1234405741</when>\n<utime>02/12/09 04:29 AM</utime>\n</post>"}